		</div>
	</div>
	<div class="commentBody">
		<div id="comment_body_64156181">So get your news from a multitude of sources, recognize the bias of each, take it all with a grain of salt, and use a bit of common sense to reason it all out. I regularly switch between NYT, US News, AP, NPR, CS Monitor, and a couple of others. I watch CNN to see what the more liberal spin on events is. I watch Fox News to stay on top of whatever batshit outrage-of-the-week my relatives will be ranting about today. I follow Reuters for a less US-centric viewpoint, and same with Al Jazeera. If you either trust one source blindly or decide to blanket ignore them all, you're doing it wrong.</div>
	</div>

